Requires the Flask library

To Execute :
    call init_database() of main.py once
    To do so, write the following two lines in the python3 interpreter
        1-from main import init_database
        2-init_database()
    Then execute the program using
        python3 main.py
    Log in using 
        username : default
        password : admin
    Access using a web browser and the given address, in my case 127.0.0.1:5000
    Note : You may need to add /login to the address to be redirected to a proper page

Uses the Flask framework to provide an html gui and sqlite server to the Employee Management system

Scripts :
    main.py : interacts with database, provides proper web pages and feedback (error messages) using flask.
Templates :
    add.html : Form required to add an employee
        returns fields [id, firstname, lastname, department] (all text boxes)
    options.html : presents the four possible actions
        returns field [choice], value dependant of toggled radio button
    remove.html : form required to remove an employee
        presents a list of employees, with buttons to remove the corresponding employee
    search.html : form required to look for an employee
        returns field [id], text box
    login.html/logout.html :
    layout.html : provides basic layout of html components. All previous files extend layout.html
    

        

